<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFB1EF71FF42F9CBFF45FE31" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB1EF72FF42F9CBFC23F890" blockId="25.[151,1437,1589,1869]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB1EF72FF42F9CBFEE7F920" bold="true" box="[199,338,1662,1688]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Comments:</emphasis>
This species are so rare as 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB1EF72FDFBF9CAFD40F920" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1907" box="[638,757,1662,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Hyperophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB1EF72FDFBF9CAFD40F920" box="[638,757,1662,1688]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">H. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and only one individual was collected in a light trap. Despite the brief description provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB1EF72FD97F916FCC1F904" author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C." box="[530,884,1698,1725]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 401" refId="ref29469" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1878) Monographie der Phaneropteriden. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 28, 1 - 401." type="journal article" year="1878">Brunner von Wattenwyl (1878)</bibRefCitation>
, the characters are consistent with the individual registered here. The general colour of the individual is green (turning yellowish after being pinned and dried), the pronotal disc is crimson, as the pronotal carina and the upper third of the lateral lobes of the pronotum, these latter presenting punctuations of the same colour in their lower two thirds.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB1EF72FF42F887FDF8F8F4" blockId="25.[151,1437,1589,1869]" box="[199,589,1842,1869]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB1EF72FF42F887FEEEF8F4" bold="true" box="[199,347,1842,1868]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
: Sound not recorded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB2EF71FF12FF22FD5BFF09" blockId="26.[151,750,151,177]" box="[151,750,151,177]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB2EF71FF12FF22FD5BFF09" bold="true" box="[151,750,151,177]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
3.2. Cosmophylla 
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB2EF71FEF3FF22FD5BFF09" author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C." box="[374,750,151,177]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 401" refId="ref29469" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1878) Monographie der Phaneropteriden. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 28, 1 - 401." type="journal article" year="1878">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB2EF71FF12FF6AFF45FE31" blockId="26.[151,1437,223,393]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
This small group presents 10 species and six genera, with representants from the Neotropics, South American Transition Zone, Andean, Australian and Ethiopic regions. Only the genus 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB2EF71FC3CFEB1FBADFEA5" box="[953,1048,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Engonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB2EF71FC3CFEB1FBADFEA5" box="[953,1048,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Engonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was so far recorded, having three currently described species. 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB2EF71FE54FE9DFD85FEF9" box="[465,560,296,321]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Engonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB2EF71FE54FE9DFD85FEF9" box="[465,560,296,321]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Engonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only genus of Cosmophylla encountered in the neotropics and no species was known to occur in southern 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFFB2EF71FD8CFEFEFDF8FEDD" box="[521,589,331,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Brazil</collectingCountry>
so far. Here we provide records for 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB2EF71FC6CFEF9FB26FEDD" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[1001,1171,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Engonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB2EF71FC6CFEF9FB26FEDD" box="[1001,1171,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Engonia minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and for a possibly new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
